    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@bobylito it's part of the \"conventional commits\" approach, which uses \"fix\" when a commit should bump a patch version or \"chore\" when it can stay the same. The default Renovate approach is that changes to dependencies are a \"fix\" as they could change behaviour and hence should bump minor version or more",
