  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "If you want, it’s possible to configure node or engine updates for fix too. Best to set that in your algolia preset\n\n________________________________\nFrom: Alex S <notifications@github.com>\nSent: Monday, March 12, 2018 4:33:58 PM\nTo: algolia/instantsearch.js\nCc: Rhys Arkins; Mention\nSubject: Re: [algolia/instantsearch.js] fix(deps): update dependency events to v1.1.1 (#2804)\n\n\n@bobylito<https://github.com/bobylito> it's part of the \"conventional commits\" approach, which uses \"fix\" when a commit should bump a patch version or \"chore\" when it can stay the same. The default Renovate approach is that changes to dependencies are a \"fix\" as they could change behaviour and hence should bump minor version or more\n\nI'm not sure of the interpretation of conventional commit from renovate here. For example, this PR is a fix but the update is a patch version. But the node version (8.4.0 to 8.9.4) is a chore #2803<https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/pull/2803>\n\n—\nYou are receiving this because you were mentioned.\nReply to this email directly, view it on GitHub<https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/pull/2804#issuecomment-372352544>, or mute the thread<https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/AGBPaHNPxLqIQUbPALyiJBFnGJHpdrdhks5tdpVlgaJpZM4SljP8>.\n",
